Sri Lanka Gets Proposal for $700 Million Heavy Industry Zone

-- B y   A n u s h a   O n d a a t j i e
-- 
2011-02-24T09:31:16Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-02-24/sri-lanka-gets-proposal-for-700-million-heavy-industry-zone.html
  Sri Lanka  received a proposal from a
group led by an Australian firm to set up a heavy industry zone,
with an initial investment of $700 million, according to the
government’s website.  Sri Lanka’s cabinet has decided the proposed zone could be
established in the Sampur area of the northeastern port district
of Trincomalee, it said.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Anusha Ondaatjie in Colombo at 
 anushao@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
